From Connect 20205 -- Saw her there.  She is purposely waiting a few months to move forward with Voxo until she gets some folks back in the office. I'm followin gher lead and voxo's lead.
6/10/2025 -- Emailing Jacqueline to tell her I'm following her lead on timing.

McCoy Tygart Drug","105","4","Lead",,,"VOXO",,,,,,"Casey Hedden","casey@mccoytygartdrug.com",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"False","False",,"False",,,"False","False",,,,,,,"6/10/2025 --> From Email from Casey -- We have 4 stores in a 30 mile radius that we need to get VPN connected with each other. A not-so-distant goal is to get a centralized data entry location for these store setup, with central fill a secondary goal.
Woodlands Pharmacy - already a VOXO user
McCoy Tygart Drug - currently using Vow - has a static IP address
Sheridan Family Pharmacy - currently using Vow - ISP modem in pass through mode
Redfield Pharmacy - currently using MedTel - not sure about their setup, have an employee who understands most of this stuff, I'll have him look into it
Pioneer Central Office Server - located at McCoy Tygart Drug with VPN to Sheridan Family Pharmacy
6/11/25 -- I spoke with Kaycee this morning for abou
t 30 minutes. He has four locations. One is on Voxo and the other three are not yet on Voxo. The one that's on Voxo is still on a Vow

firewall. They need all of the locations on a VPN so anybody at any location can remotely access the pioneer system at any other location. I need to speak with the guy at Pioneer about this just to make sure to straightforward as I think it is, but that shouldn't be too complicated conversation. I'm also going to talk to the engineers at rhino about the set up in which firewalls to use. One of the locations is a larger location with 15 to 20 computers and a half a dozen a dozen printers. The other locations are much smaller than that. Nothing in this should be too complicated, but he did want to make absolutely sure that we don't break the phones while we're in the middle of bringing up the van's network. I assured him we would not do that and that we will coordinate tightly with Voxo to make sure everything works. Seamlessly and downtime is minimal to nonexistent.

Vital Care Infusion Services","108",,"Lead",,,,,,,"Jonathan Sims",,"Jonathan Sims",,"601-596-2800",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"False","False",,"False",,,"False","False",,,,,,,"Per Levi at Voxo I called Blake Tubbs to discuss needs for both of these businesses to have new IT support.  Blake gave me a quick run down and said that I needed to speak with the owner Jonathan Sims.  His number is primary contact on this and The Compounder

I spoke with Jonathan. He has a vital care pharmacy and the compounder here in Hattiesburg. Vital care is a franchise and he also has another one in Baton Rouge. He has need for firewall management and also for PC management although vital care is probably gonna handle a PC management for him at least for those two franchises. He may still need PC management for the compounder but doesn't like the idea of paying on a model that is a paper person model, which is what somebody in Jackson gave him. Paper machine model is what vinyl care is going to do and I told him that if I care couldn't handle everything for him that I could help him find a good support mechanism to handle the compounder. I'm going to go by there after I get back in town from this trip and look at his network at vital care and also at the compounder and just look at what's needed there whether it's just a firewall or whether we need to replace switches and APs and things like that. His preference is going to be to not replacing anything more than he has to, but also understands that that means that there'll be unmanaged equipment in the building that if it fails is going to take a couple of days to get something in that's about it for now I just need to call him back as soon as I get back in town.
